<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Empty Nest" plays to a full house every week on NBC. 
</P>
<P>
Nestled between "The Golden Girls" and "Hunter" on Saturdays at 9:30 p.m., the 
first-year comedy is a winner in the ratings, consistently landing among prime 
time's Top 10 shows. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Mulligan -- surrounded on the cover by co-stars David Leisure, Kristy 
McNichol, Dinah Manoff, Park Overall and the dog Bear -- plays Miami 
pediatrician Harry Weston. When he's not treating his young patients, Harry 
copes with life as a widower and his two protective daughters (McNichol and 
Manoff). 
</P>
<P>
Harry has yet to find a new mate, but lonely he's not. The show's writers are 
seeing to it that those daughters aren't the only women in his life . . . 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Richard Mulligan -- surrounded on the cover by co-stars David 
Leisure, Kristy McNichol, Dinah Manoff, Park Overall and the dog Bear -- plays 
Miami pediatrician Harry Weston. Steve Fontanini / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
