THE BIG MIX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I believe we all want the various ethnic groups of the Los Angeles area to 
nurture, support and thus perpetuate their roots. 
</P>
<P>
But then: Assuming all of the minorities develop their own museums, theaters, 
etc., will they join the soon-to-be-minority white upper and middle classes in 
filling the seats at the Music Center and elsewhere? 
</P>
<P>
Will the existence of Disney Hall and the Dance Gallery be justified? Will MOCA 
and LACMA continue to be successful? Interesting thought, yes? 
</P>
<P>
CONRAD J. DOERR 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
