<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH'S UNVEILS BUDGET PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yes, President Bush's "Good Start on the Environment" (editorial, Feb. 10) is 
indeed a welcome change in attitude from the recent past, and it is a relief to 
know that he is willing to postpone the proposed oil-lease sale off our coast. 
</P>
<P>
However, it must be recognized that the California coast is anything but a 
pristine territory; wherein the Wildlife Refuge on the north coast of Alaska is 
precisely this -- pristine. That the President is ready to degrade Alaska's 
Wildlife Refuge is evidence that he will abandon environmental progress any 
time it conflicts with private exploitation of public resources; and this is 
hardly environmental progress for its own value. 
</P>
<P>
We need a kinder and a wiser concept of the ecology than the President evinces. 
</P>
<P>
NORMA JOHNSON 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
