<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE AIR FARE CONTROVERSY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Simross wrote about shopping for emergency air fares where there is a death in 
the family. Recently I researched this problem for myself and found that Delta 
Airlines has an exceptional program. They offer a 35% discount for all family 
members traveling to a funeral from within the continental United States. This 
would include whether or not you are traveling with the remains as required by 
some of the airlines. 
</P>
<P>
It is also a specific policy as opposed to whatever relief may be gained from a 
supervisor. The phone number is (800) DL CARES. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT L. KAILES 
</P>
<P>
Playa del Rey 
</P>
<P>
 The Delta Airlines DL CARES program is unusual in the airline business because 
the carrier has an 800 number for consumers to dial in case of a death in the 
family. The requirement for the 35% discount on a regular coach fare is only 
that Delta must be shipping the remains of the deceased. Family members do not 
have to fly on the same flight with the body. Family members may get the 
discounted funeral fare from Delta up to one day prior to the shipping of the 
body and up to 21 days after. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
