<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 DIE, 60 HURT AS FIRE HITS RESIDENTIAL HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire ripped through an aging residential hotel early Friday, killing four 
people and injuring nearly 60 others, including four police officers, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said it appears the four-alarm blaze started in an apartment on 
the first floor of the Billinghurst Hotel, forcing many trapped residents to 
jump from upper-story windows. The blaze was under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
