<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN ARRESTED IN SHOOTING DEATH OF RAMONA RESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GENE YASUDA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men have been arrested in the slaying of a Ramona man, a Sheriff's 
Department spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Devies Miller, 42, of Ramona and Thomas Gilbert Costa, 40, of Santa 
Ysabel were arrested at Miller's home Friday in connection with the shooting 
death of Benjamin Gomez-Munoz, 29, said Lt. Bill Baxter of the homicide 
division. 
</P>
<P>
According to authorities, Gomez-Munoz and three companions were riding in a 
vehicle near Miller's home Friday, when Gomez-Munoz's car caught fire. The 
three companions went to a nearby home to get buckets of water, while 
Gomez-Munoz stayed with the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
When the three companions returned to the car they found Gomez-Munoz suffering 
from a gunshot wound to the chest. 
</P>
<P>
The three companions took Gomez-Munoz to a nearby health clinic, where he died 
before emergency personnel could take him to a hospital, sheriff's deputies 
said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation by deputies and interviews with the victim's companions led 
authorities to Miller's home, 27067 Highway 78 East. GENE YASUDA 
</P>
</TEXT>
