<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOLLOWERS SOUGHT FOR A NEW 'REVOLUTION' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Our country has gone through a lot of different kinds of revolutions in its 
history. I truly believe it is time for us to have another one: an 
environmental revolution! We are losing our beautiful natural resources to the 
land developers, oil companies, industrialists and corrupt politicians. 
</P>
<P>
Our water is polluted by industrial waste, our oceans by oil spills. Our hills 
and canyons are disappearing in alarming numbers to the greedy developers, our 
air is unbreathable much of the time and our elected officials are selling us 
out to the highest bidder. Our wildlife is endangered and so are we human 
beings. 
</P>
<P>
We can stop this if we join together. 
</P>
<P>
I have always had great sympathy for the American Indians. Now I can feel 
empathy with them. The sick, helpless, powerless feeling I get when I see giant 
bulldozers and land movers on the prowl must be what the Indians felt like when 
they saw the wagon trains and buffalo hunters approaching. Must such a shameful 
history repeat itself over and over again? 
</P>
<P>
Once our canyons, hills, water and animals are gone, it will be too late to 
save them. The time is now. I urge you to join our environmental revolution 
today. There are many groups already formed and more being formed daily. Please 
get involved. We need you! 
</P>
<P>
JUDY ROSE 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
