<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CSUN REBOUNDS WITH 7-4 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chae-Ho Chong hit a two-run home run and Robert Wheatcroft pitched a six-hitter 
Saturday to lead host Cal State Northridge to a 7-4 nonconference victory over 
St. Mary's. 
</P>
<P>
Behind, 3-1, Northridge tied the score in the fifth inning then took a 5-3 lead 
on Chong's blast in the seventh. John Bonilla, who had singled to open the 
inning, scored ahead of Chong. Mike Solar went four for four for CSUN, which 
had 14 hits but committed four errors. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors (5-1), who came back from a crushing 15-2 loss to Cal State Long 
Beach on Friday, will again play host to St. Mary's today, at noon. Wheatcroft 
(3-0) struck out four and walked one in pitching his second complete game. 
</P>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Mission 8, Palomar 5 -- Jose Garcia allowed only one earned run in 7 2/3 
innings for the victory and Manuel Orozco had two hits and two runs batted in 
as Mission picked up its first win in the nonconference game at Palomar. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Romo and John Kukawski each doubled and singled for Mission. Garcia gave 
up eight hits and struck out four before Tony Margoles relieved him in the 
eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 4-7, Whittier 2-1 -- The Kingsmen received superb pitching from 
Jay Anderson and Kevin O'Neill to sweep the nonconference doubleheader at 
Whittier. Anderson (1-1) pitched a complete game in the opener, allowing two 
unearned runs on three hits and no walks. 
</P>
<P>
Pt. Loma 9-6, The Master's 4-7 -- The Mustangs scored two runs in the bottom of 
the ninth inning of the second game to gain a split in the NAIA District 3 
doubleheader at Pt. Loma. Russ Henzie led off with a pinch-hit single and Matt 
Price followed with a pinch-hit double, Henzie stopping at third. Henzie scored 
when Craig Johnson grounded to short and Randy Tippitt overthrew first base. 
</P>
