<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO REAL WRESTLERS CLAIM 5TH CONSECUTIVE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Camino Real High wrestlers won six of 12 weight divisions and placed second 
in two others to win their fifth consecutive Valley League title Saturday at El 
Camino Real. 
</P>
<P>
The Conquistadores scored 202 points to the 163 1/2 of runner-up San Fernando. 
Canoga Park (146), Birmingham (91), Granada Hills (42) and Chatsworth (34 1/2) 
rounded out the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
Greg McMurray defeated Marcus Quek of Chatsworth, 6-0, in the 112-pound final 
to improve his record to 31-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021989-0128 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 20703 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 19, 1989, Sunday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 19; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
436 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
WILSON GATHERS 22 POINTS AS HART ADVANCES ON HISTORIC EVENING, 62-35 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE In another second-round 5-A game: Thousand Oaks 68, Edison 53 -- 
Thousand O 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Hart High girls' basketball team, ranked second in the Southern Section 5-A 
Division, won its first-ever playoff game, 62-35, Saturday night in a 
second-round match-up over visiting Norco. 
</P>
<P>
Six-foot-three-inch forward Sara Wilson scored a game-high 22 points, 14 in the 
second half, and pulled down 12 rebounds for Hart, which recorded its 12th 
consecutive victory. 
</P>
<P>
The Indians led, 26-17, at intermission and extended their advantage to 41-22 
with 1:31 remaining in the third quarter by posting a 15-5 run, during which 
Wilson contributed eight points. 
</P>
<P>
Hart widened the margin again to 57-28 in the final period, erupting for a 12-4 
run, sparked by Wilson and guard Anjanette Dione, who each scored four points. 
Dione finished with 16 points. MIKE GLAZE In another second-round 5-A game: 
Thousand Oaks 68, Edison 53 -- Thousand Oaks made 26 of 37 free throws, 
including 12 of 18 in the fourth quarter of the game at Thousand Oaks. Shani 
Smyth and Amy Chandler each scored 22 points for Thousand Oaks (23-4) and 
teammate Michelle Palmisano added 17. Thousand Oaks broke the game open by 
outscoring Edison, 19-11, in the third quarter.5-AA DIVISION Simi Valley 76, El 
Toro 58 -- Keira Irwin scored 14 points, handed out nine assists and grabbed 
six rebounds to help Simi Valley past the South Coast Conference runner-up at 
Simi Valley. The Pioneers ran off to a 19-9 lead in the first period and were 
never really threatened. Shannon Solway led all scorers with 25 points for Simi 
Valley.3-A DIVISION Alemany 55, Lompoc 51 -- Andrea Hoffman sank a basket with 
43 seconds to play to give the Indians a two-point lead in the game at Lompoc. 
Hoffman scored a game-high 24 points and pulled down 12 rebounds and Anne 
Sasadeusz added 14 points and Sylvia Castaneda had 10 points for Alemany 
(19-5).2-A DIVISION La Reina 64, Regina Caeli 42 -- Amy Alarian scored a 
team-high 15 points and Heather Freeman added 14 points for the host Regents. 
After a close first quarter, the Regents (20-5) outscored Regina Caeli, 28-18, 
in the next two quarters to take a 42-30 lead.1-A DIVISION La Sierra Academy 
46, Montclair Prep 39 -- The Mounties had only six points in the first quarter 
and trailed throughout the game at Montclair Prep. Nikki Smith led the Mounties 
with a game-high 20 points and had 21 rebounds. Silver Valley 50, Oakwood 49 (2 
OTs) -- Nancy Phillips sank a free throw with five seconds left in double 
overtime to lift the Trojans at Oakwood. Bishop Diego 54, L.A. Baptist 34 -- 
The Knights had 22 turnovers and were outscored in every quarter of the game at 
L.A. Baptist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
