CRA APPROVES TWO SHELTERS FOR HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Funding has been approved by the Community Redevelopment Agency for two shelter 
projects in the Central City East area for the city's homeless. 
</P>
<P>
The board approved a $300,600 loan for the St. Vincent DePaul Shelter to help 
complete a 70-bed day facility at 231 Winston St. and $58,034 in operating 
funds for the Los Angeles Men's Place (known as LAMP), an 18-bed day shelter 
for the mentally ill homeless. 
</P>
