<HEADLINE>
<P>
FACTORY HOME PRODUCTION IN STATE 12,003 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California's manufactured-home industry sold 12,003 homes last year of which 
10,457 were sited in the state, with the remainder exported to other states, 
according to the California Manufactured Housing Institute. 
</P>
<P>
The institute said more than 1 million Californians live in more than 540,000 
manufactured houses. The cost of the average manufactured house sold during 
1988 was $37,230, excluding the cost of the land, according to Tony Hadley, 
spokesman for the institute. 
</P>
<P>
Hadley said construction cost for a manufactured house averaged $30.99 per 
square foot compared to $43.40 a square foot for a comparable site-constructed 
house. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
