<P>
3 GIS INJURED IN BUS BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Americans were wounded, one seriously, when unidentified assailants 
hurled a bomb at a bus carrying 28 U.S. soldiers north of the Honduran capital 
of Tegucigalpa, the U.S. Embassy said. Two Honduran passers-by were also 
injured, police said. An embassy spokeswoman said the Americans were returning 
to the military base at Palmerola after a brief training exercise in Comayagua, 
about 40 miles northwest of the capital, at the time of the attack. It was the 
second attack on American troops in the country this month. On Feb. 1, seven 
vehicles carrying more than 30 U.S. soldiers were attacked by gunmen in 
northern Honduras, but no one was injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
