<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES NAMED CALIFORNIA'S BEST PAPER FOR SECOND YEAR IN A ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second year in a row, The Times has won top honors from the California 
Newspaper Publishers Assn. for general excellence among papers with a daily 
circulation above 75,000, it was announced Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
It was the third time The Times has won the general excellence award in the 
last four years. 
</P>
<P>
The Times also won the CNPA's first prize for an editorial series, regardless 
of circulation. In addition, the paper finished first among large papers in 
awards given for editorial cartooning, sports coverage, business and financial 
coverage and arts and entertainment coverage. 
</P>
<P>
Among other large papers in California, the Santa Rosa Press Democrat and the 
San Jose Mercury News each took five top awards, the Orange County Register 
took three, the Sacramento Union won two and the Bakersfield Californian, the 
Sacramento Bee, the San Francisco Examiner, the San Diego Union, the San 
Bernardino County Sun and the Long Beach Press-Telegram each took one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES; CALIFORNIA NEWSPAPER PUBLISHERS ASSOCIATION; AWARDS; 
NEWSPAPERS -- CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
