<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PAYTON LEADS OREGON ST. TO 40-POINT WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Payton scored 19 of his 31 points in the second half as Oregon State dealt 
Washington a 106-66 loss -- the Huskies' third-worst defeat ever -- in a 
Pacific 10 Conference game Saturday at Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
Washington's 40-point losing margin was topped only by a 55-point defeat, 
116-61, at Arizona earlier this season, and a 52-point rout by UCLA in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Knox scored 22 points for the Beavers (18-5 overall, 10-4 in the Pac-10), 
while Teo Alibegovic had 17. Eldridge Recasner and Mark West scored 12 points 
each for Washington (10-14, 6-9). 
</P>
<P>
Washington State 60, Oregon 54 -- Harold Wright scored all five of his points 
and added a clutch steal in the final 36 seconds to help the Cougars down the 
Ducks at Pullman, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Quinnett scored 17 points for Washington State (8-15, 3-11), and his 
basket with 8:14 left gave the Cougars a 46-32 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Helms had eight of his 18 points in a 22-9 run by Oregon (8-16, 3-11) that 
included 10 straight points. Helms' jumper with 1:09 left cut Washington 
State's lead to 55-54. 
</P>
<P>
Wright entered the game for the first time with 52 seconds left and made a 
three-point play with 36 seconds left, then added two free throws with 25 
seconds remaining. 
</P>
