<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HOWELL SCORES 46 POINTS, BUT TROJANS LOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior guard Karon Howell scored 46 points to break a USC and Pacific 10 
Conference single-game scoring record, but it was not enough as the USC women's 
basketball team lost to Arizona, 94-84, Saturday night at Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
Cherie Nelson, considered the star player on the team, played only 4 minutes. 
No explanation was offered as to why Nelson didn't play more. 
</P>
<P>
Howell made 17-of-29 field-goal attempts, including six-of-12 three-point 
shots. The performance broke Cheryl Miller's four-year school record of 45 
points. Howell also broke the conference record of 45 points, set in 1987 by 
Jennifer Bennett of California. 
</P>
<P>
USC is 5-7 in the Pac-10 and 9-13 overall. Arizona is 3-9 and 8-14. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona State 86, UCLA 73 -- UCLA dropped below the .500 mark in Pacific 10 
play with its loss to the Sun Devils at Tempe, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
The Sun Devils, who lost to the Bruins at UCLA, 85-81, in January, were led by 
guard Karen O'Conner, who scored 20 points, and forward Fran Ciak, who had 16 
points and 12 rebounds. Rochelle Roulier had 16 points for the Bruins. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins dropped to 5-6 in conference play and 9-12 overall, as they were 
outrebounded 54-37 by the Sun Devils. Arizona State is 3-10 and 9-14. 
</P>
<P>
CS Long Beach 91, San Diego State 80 -- Penny Toler scored 24 points to lead 
the 49ers (22-4 overall, 15-0 in the Big West Conference) over the Aztecs 
(21-5, 12-5) at San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Traci Waites and Dana Wilkerson each scored 16 for the 49ers. Angelica Jackson 
had 29 for San Diego State. 
</P>
