<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lars-Boerje Eriksson became the first Swede to win a speed race on the World 
Cup skiing tour by winning a men's World Cup super giant slalom by a 
three-hundredths of a second over West Germany's Markus Wasmeier. 
</P>
<P>
Swedish skiers have never excelled in downhill or super-G because of the lack 
of long, steep slopes in Scandinavia. 
</P>
<P>
Eriksson earned his first World Cup victory in 1 minute 17.98 seconds. Wasmeier 
finished in 1:18.01, and Helmut Mayer of Austria was third in 1:18.29. A giant 
slalom is scheduled today. 
</P>
