<TEXT>
<P>
Pernell Whitaker, showing no ill effects of a twice-broken left hand, won the 
International Boxing Federation lightweight title at Hampton, Va., with a 
12-round unanimous decision over Greg Haugen (23-2) of Auburn, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
Whitaker (17-1), of Norfolk, Va., incurred his only loss last March, when he 
broke his hand for the second time while fighting Jose Luis Ramirez for the 
World Boxing Council lightweight title. 
</P>
<P>
Whitaker became the sixth member of the 1984 U.S. Olympic team to win a world 
title. 
