<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENTS' DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday marks the observance of Presidents' Day, a holiday created to celebrate 
both Washington's and Lincoln's birthdays. It is a federal holiday that falls 
on the third Monday of each February. Actually, Lincoln's birthday falls on 
Feb. 12 and Washington's birthday on Feb. 22. 
</P>
<P>
Open Monday: Most stores. Rapid Transit District buses will follow regular 
schedules. 
</P>
<P>
Closed Monday: All government offices, courts, banks, post offices, stock and 
commodity exchanges, libraries, schools and many businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
