Presley's "Burning Love," the Temptations' "Papa Was a Rolling Stone" and Derek 
and the Dominoes' "Layla." Other possibilities in 1974 included Elton John's 
"Don't Let the Sun Go Down on Me," Stevie Wonder's "You Haven't Done Nothin" or 
"Living for the City," and Joni Mitchell's "Help Me." 
</P>
