<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UC IRVINE TEAMS HAVE EASY TIME IN TRACK MEETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine's men's and women's track and field teams scored easy victories over 
Cal State Long Beach and Cal Poly Pomona Saturday in a nonconference meet at 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Junior Mike Morales, a Garden Grove High School graduate, won the hammer throw 
(192 feet 6inches), the shotput (51-6) and the discus (168-9) to pace the 
Anteater men, who won the meet with 119.5 points. Long Beach was second with 43 
points and Pomona third with 24 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
Marc Goulet won the 800 meters (1:56.2) and the mile (4:15.9), and sophomore 
Matt Farmer won the long jump (22-11 1/2) and the high jump (6-6 3/4) to help 
Irvine (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, Irvine won with 90 points, followed by Long Beach 
(28) and Pomona (18). 
</P>
<P>
Trindl Fearnley won the javelin in the third-best throw in the school's history 
(137-11), and ran the third leg on Irvine's winning 4 x 400 meter relay. Junior 
Brigid Stirling helped Irvine with a victory in the 1,500 meters (4:38.3) and 
tied teammate Beth McGrann for first place in the 3,000 (9:59.2). 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference softball doubleheader: 
</P>
<P>
Loyola Marymount 5-2, Southern California College 3-5 -- Kristin Heather gave 
up five hits through seven innings to lead Loyola Marymount (3-3) in the first 
game at SCC. In the second game, Suzie Hopkins (2-1) gave up seven hits in 
seven innings for SCC (2-3). 
</P>
<P>
In men's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Hawaii 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Carlos Briceno had 17 kills and Allen Allen added 16 
to lead visiting Hawaii, 15-9, 15-9, 15-10. 
</P>
<P>
At the San Diego Intercollegiate men's tennis tournament: 
</P>
<P>
