<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: PRESIDENT'S DAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is observed as President's Day, marking the birthdays of Presidents 
George Washington and Abraham Lincoln. Following is a list of local closings. 
</P>
<P>
GOVERNMENT: Federal, state and county offices will be closed Monday. City 
offices in Westminster will be open Monday; all other city offices will be 
closed. 
</P>
<P>
MAIL: Mail will not be delivered Monday. 
</P>
<P>
TRASH: Trash will not be picked up on Monday in Anaheim, Brea, Buena Park, 
Cypress, Garden Grove, Placentia and Yorba Linda. In all other cities, pickup 
schedules remain unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
COURTS: County, state and federal courts will be closed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
BANKS: Most banks will close on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOLS: In the Saddleback Valley Unified School District, schools will be 
closed Monday through Wednesday. All other public schools will be closed only 
Monday. 
</P>
