<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION WRESTLING; 
</P>
<P>
FOUR COUNTY WRESTLERS WIN IN 2-A 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange County proved itself something of a wrestling powerhouse at the Southern 
Section 2-A championships at Nogales High School Saturday by placing three 
schools in the top 10 and producing four individual champions. 
</P>
<P>
Atascadero won the team championship before the final round started and 
finished with 118 1/2 points. Laguna Hills was second with 91, Buena Park was 
third with 88 1/2 and Mater Dei finished fifth with 78 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
Heath Sims of Woodbridge, a state champion last year in the 132-pound division, 
won the 138-pound division with a pin of Mater Dei's Troy Monge with 1 minute 
45 seconds left in the second period. 
</P>
<P>
"I had seen him wrestle before, but I never wrestled him," Sims said. "I 
thought he would be a little stronger." 
</P>
<P>
Sims seemed to wear down Monge, who had an attacking style but had difficulty 
maintaining advantages against Sims. 
</P>
<P>
Sims was stronger and has wrestled in the 145- and 154-pound divisions this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
Three other county wrestlers won their weight titles: Greg Andres of Sunny 
Hills (105), Brian Bertrand of Buena Park (126) and Gabino Aguilar of Orange 
(132). ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
